title: After Third Straight Win, UMD Up to No. 21
text:
After Third Straight Win, UMD Up to No. 21 
By Zach Schneider After Third Straight Win, UMD Up to No. 21 October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 3:24 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team moved up four spots to No. 21 in this week's American Football Coaches' Association (AFCA) Division II poll, which was released on Monday afternoon. 
The Bulldogs beat St. Cloud State 34-27 this past Saturday, marking UMD's third straight win. The move up in the poll ends the team's three-week stay at No. 25 in the nation. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
For full results of this week's AFCA Division II poll, click here. 
UMD is (4-2) overall this season and this Saturday is on the road to Mary, with kickoff scheduled for 2:30 p.m.
